dismissalText.commentary: Murali Vijay run out (Utseya/†Taylor) 11 (24b 1x4 0x6 40m) SR: 45.83

dismissalComment.html: Vijay is run out. Absolutely lazy effort from Vijay and smart work from Taylor. It was tapped past square-leg .. Vijay had stepped out looking for the second run but gets back. Here is where the drama starts. The throw comes to the front of the stumps and Taylor collects and back flicks it to the stumps ...Vijay is so lazy out there .. he was so slow .. and lands his bat down and drags ever so slowly .. unbelievably lazy. And he is run out. Thank you come again ..

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli run out (Chigumbura) 0 (0b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: Kohli is run out. It was reverse paddled towards short third man and they decide to get across for the risky single. Chigumbura, who has had an awful time with the ball so far, fires in a lovely direct hit .. Kohli tried to dive back into the crease but couldn't beat the throw. Out without facing a ball. In street cricket, if you had owned the bat, you would have taken it and walked off in a huff!

commentTextItems.html: That must taste real sweet. Zimbabwe have clinched a comfortable win. They have done it with 10 balls to spare. It was the short delivery and Chigumbura goes for the pull and top edges it over the keeper. Fabulous innings from Ervine. And Chigumbura made sure the debutant's effort didn't go to waste.

commentPostTextItems.html: The stronger team won the day. Simple as that. It was absolutely top effort from Ervine. Right from the start, he looked so cool, so collected and in control.  Much credit to Taylor who laid the platform with a responsible innings.

Sudha: "As an Indian supporter, am a bit disappointed. But what a game by Zimbabwe and Erwine! But when a country has seen such a turmoil on the political and economic fronts, its amazing to see the never-say-die spirit in the way they played today. Congratulations to Zimbabwe. "
Please hang on for the quotes from the post-match ceremony.

Suresh Raina: "They batted really well. They had a good partnership. We didn't bowl well, couple of guys are playing their first games. hopefully we will learn from this. Mishra bowled well, Jadeja too. We need to work on our bowling and fielding department and come back."

Chigumbura: "I left the team down a bit in the morning with my bowling. The batsmen played really well. Only one seamer, Chris, bowled well but the spinners bowled really well for us. It was a good start .. credit for Ervine and he has to make sure that he gets consistent. He played very well today."

Man of the Match is Brendon Taylor: " I am very happy. It (man of the match) doesn't come often. I have always enjoyed my keeping. We basically wanted to bat through. Try not to lose too many wickets and give it a go later. We just wanted to knock it around in the middle overs. We knew Elton and Blignaut and Coventry to come in. It was a good all round performance on a flat wicket. It was nice to see all the guys chipping in."
That's it from us. The stronger team won the day. Simple as that. Thanks for logging on.

commentTextItems.html: Another full toss and what's more it was on the leg stump! Ervine was not going to miss out on that one; he lifts it over midwicket
Ervine rocks! He goes down on his knee, fetches the full toss from outside off and sweeps it to the square-leg boundary.
rushes down the track and has a big heave .. doesn't connect well but the ball rolls to deep midwicket
full and on the legs ... Ervine tries to whip it to the on side and slices it towards long-on

commentPreTextItems.html: Robert Brown: "now it is keeping one's head.  Noting rash and Zimbabwe win.:

commentTextItems.html: full delivery outside off, driven to long-off
full and straight, driven down to long-on . End of the over.

commentPostTextItems.html: Check out ESPNF1 where's it's a mixed day for Jenson Button. After it was revealed he has split from the lovely Jessica Michibata, he bounced back by setting the fastest time of the day in free practice for Sunday's Turkish Grand Prix. Click here to read more

commentTextItems.html: That's the game breaker, surely? Dinda slips in a full toss and Chigumbura whacks it over mid-off
charges down the track, Dinda fires it full and the ball goes under the big swing of the bat and to DK
yorker from Dinda but Ervine stays calm, doesn't have a big back-lift and runs it to third man
reaches forward to squeeze the full delivery to right of third man for couple of runs
full toss but no run. hmmm .. it was outside off and Ervine went for the cover drive but made contact with the bottom of the bat
What a fabulicious thwack! The Zimbabwe captain clears the front foot and smashes the length delivery to the wide midwicket boundary.
yorker length on the middle and off, turned to midwicket

he loves those pull shots. Yummy! It was short in length and Ervine pulls it to the midwicket boundary. Yusuf rushes after it and makes a diving stop.  his elbow has touched the boundary line as he was about to push it back. ... Third umpire, rightly, reckons it's a four. And stand up and applaud. It's fifty for the debutant. Calm. Cool. solid. very impressive.

commentPreTextItems.html: Raina has a chat with Umesh. 34 from 28 balls

commentTextItems.html: really full delivery, short of the blockhole, edged his off drive to the pad
Four more. The school boys are dancing in the crowd. It was the bouncer and Chigumbura top edged his pull shot over the keeper.

commentPreTextItems.html: Batting Powerplay taken Now then now then .. Much fun.

commentTextItems.html: Blasted! Immense fun. Game on. Full pitched around off stump and driven well to the left of mid-off.

dismissalComment.html: Taylor is gone. Not a great delivery but it gets a wicket. It was a short delivery on the leg stump line and Taylor pulls but finds the man at fine leg. Taylor out for 81. Now then .. who is going to take ownership of the chase? Ervine has looked good so far

headshotImage.longCaption: Charles Coventry player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Lovely slower one to remove Charles.   It looped across, dipped rapidly on a length and Coventry was completely bewildered. He lunged forward in the end and stabbed at it. The ball went on straight to go through the bat and pad gap. Vinay strikes again.

dismissalComment.html: Done in by the slider.. It landed on the middle and off line and skidded towards the middle stump line. Masakadza tried to punch it through the off side, off the back foot, but couldn't' connect as he was beaten by the in ward movement. The ball skidded through the bat and pad gap.

dismissalComment.html: Done in by the arm ball. It moves in with the arm and hits the pad in front of middle and leg. Tight call. Most likely it would have hit the leg stump. Though  no one would have complained had the umpire not given it out .. they would have then said it might have gone down the leg side.
